cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on human-authored descriptions and a novel annotation scheme for understanding such descriptions. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also likely as the dataset contains both synthetic and real-world images with visual annotations. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses the potential applications of the dataset in various visual and language tasks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper mentions a pilot experiment on visual reference resolution. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also relevant as the paper discusses the data collection method and the importance of understanding end-of-trip instructions in a taxi ride scenario for improving user experience.
